record_data.record_plain_text:
CHALK POINT STEAM, LLC RATE SCHEDULE FERC NO. 1 Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service Chalk Point Steam, LLC ("Chalk Point Steam") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service ("Reactive Supply Service") from the Chalk Point generation facility ("Facility") within the Potomac Electric Power Company zone under the operational control of PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. This Rate Schedule FERC No. 1 sets forth Chalk Point Steam's revenue requirement for Reactive Supply Service from the Facility for the units set forth below. This Rate Schedule shall be effective upon the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission. Chalk Point Steam's monthly fixed revenue requirement consists of the sum of the charges for the Facility's units specified below.
REVENUE REQUIREMENT:
Chalk Point Unit Monthly Revenue Requirement Unit 1 $38,869.11 Unit 2 $38,869.11 Total Monthly Revenue Requirement $77,738.22 Total Annual (Total Monthly x 12) $932,858.64
PARTIAL MONTH REVENUE REQUIREMENT: When a unit deactivation date ("Unit Deactivation Date") is other than the first day of the month, the revenue requirement shall be a blended revenue requirement for the month of service in which the deactivation occurred as follows: the sum of (i) the total monthly revenue requirement prior to the rate change divided by the number of days in the month of the deactivation, with the quotient then multiplied by the number of days in the month prior to the Unit Deactivation Date and (ii) the total monthly revenue requirement after the rate change divided by the number of days in the month of the deactivation, with the quotient then multiplied by the remaining number of days in the month from and including the Unit Deactivation Date.
